Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1349
S.P. 566 In Senate, April 1, 2025
the Juniper Ridge Landfill
Received by the Secretary of the Senate on March 28, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Environment and Natural Resources pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator TIPPING of Penobscot.
Cosponsored by Representative ROEDER of Bangor and
Senators: BENNETT of Oxford, NANGLE of Cumberland, Representatives: BOYER of
Poland, DILL of Old Town.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 38 MRSA ยง1304-B, sub-ยง8 is enacted to read:
3 8. Contract to operate Juniper Ridge Landfill. The department may not enter into
4 or renew a contract for the operation of the state-owned Juniper Ridge Landfill, located in
5 the City of Old Town, without the approval of the Legislature.
6 Approval of a contract under this subsection does not replace any other license required by
7 law.
8 SUMMARY
99 This bill requires the approval of the Legislature for a contract or a contract renewal
1100 for the operation of the state-owned Juniper Ridge Landfill, located in the City of Old
1111 Town.
